Subject: Sharepoint Online Activity Scan Error
Description: [Error getting INI file path from registry for host] and [PrepareTask for DC 'SHAREPOINTACCESS' for task 'System Scan' failed: Unspecified error]
DevOps_Steps_to_Reproduce__c:
Collect SPO events from NAM into NEA
NEA does not have the most up to date SP Event XML to resolve new event IDs which produces the error.
What_We_Know__c:
In SPAC log we see:
[C:53] No log location set in configuration for host and no default log location specified, will get log locations from registry
Next_Steps__c: Make sure the SPAC job is properly configured to find the activity logs for SPO
Solution_Comment__c:
The warnings regarding missing/unknown event ID are corrected with NEA v11.6. They are newer event types being collected by Activity Monitor that SA v11.5 does not have the mapping for, but they are not inhibiting the data collection.

The main issue that we were running into previous was the Activity Logs portion of the query settings was not properly configured.
https://helpcenter.netwrix.com/bundle/EnterpriseAuditor_11.6/page/Content/EnterpriseAuditor/Admin/DataCollector/SPAA/ActivityLogLocations.htm
We also discussed Agent Archiving in Activity Monitor, but opted to leave that not configured. More info on that below:
https://helpcenter.netwrix.com/bundle/ActivityMonitor_6.0/page/Content/SAM/Agents/Agent_Properties/Archiving_Tab.htm
